The paper deals with the problem of matching users with community questions in online QA websites, which involves expertise matching and social identity theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC), Computation and Language (cs.CL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Among these, cs.SI and cs.IR seem to be the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the problem of matching users with questions in online communities.
